	<!-- Introduction -->
	<purpose>
		<p>
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of the assignment of classification information to product or activity data.
	</p>
		<p>   
		This edition incorporates modifications to the previous edition listed below.
	</p>
	
	<p>
		The following ARM EXPRESS type definitions have been modified:
	</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Classification_attribute.</li>
		</ul>	
		<p>
		The following MIM EXPRESS type definitions have been added:
	</p>
		<ul>
			<li>classification_identification_item;</li>
			<li>classification_classification_item.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
		The following MIM EXPRESS type definitions have been renamed:
	</p>
		<ul>
			<li>id_for_class renamed to cwa_identification_item;</li>
			<li>version_for_class renamed to cwa_versionable_item.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
		The following MIM EXPRESS declarations have been added:
	</p>
		<ul>
			<li>classification_role in USE FROM list from management_resources_schema.</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
		Modifications made to the mapping specification of the following entity definitions:
	</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Classification_assignment.items - added;</li>
			<li>Class_hierarchy.super_class and Class_hierarchy.sub_class - removed;</li>
			<li>Classification_attribute - changed;</li>
			<li>Classification_attribute.allowed_values and Classification_attribute.characterized_class - fixed syntax errors.</li>
		</ul>
	</purpose>
	<!-- Items in scope -->
	<inscope>
		<li>assignment of classification information to product or activity data;</li>
		<li>definition of a classification with valued attributes;</li>
		<li>association of a classification with its identification in an external library;</li>
		<li>definition of a hierarchical relationship between two classes;</li>
		<li>characterization of the fact that a part or material was specified selecting particular values of parameters in a parameterized classification;</li>
		<li>identification of a classification system.</li>
	</inscope>
	<!-- Items out of scope -->
	<outscope>
		<li>representation of a library of standard parametric parts.</li>
	</outscope>
